fulltitle: Gonzalo Rubalcaba Interview Part 5 - Advice for Young Musicians
title: Gonzalo Rubalcaba Interview Part 5 - Advice for Young Musicians

description:
Welcome to Part 5 of a five-part interview with jazz virtuoso Gonzalo Rubalcaba.

Peiwen sat down with multi-Grammy award-winning jazz virtuoso Gonzalo Rubalcaba in his studio in Miami, Florida, for an in-depth conversation. He discussed his music education in Cuba, how he was discovered by Dizzy Gillespie and signed to Blue Note Records, how he has been influenced by Stravinsky and other classical music composers, and what goes through his mind as he improvises on the keyboard.

In this fifth part of the interview, Gonzalo offers advice to young musicians seeking to carve out a career in music. He says "it's not an easy career", and you have to develop the talents you've been given.
